Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: Vulnerable app not responding

Check if script has execute permissions: chmod +x vulnerable_app.py
Verify Python path in shebang line
Check log file for error messages
Issue: Interception server not capturing data

Ensure server is running: ps aux | grep intercept_server
Verify port 5000 is not in use: netcat -zv localhost 5000
Check firewall settings if accessing remotely
Issue: Payloads not executing

Verify URL encoding is correct
Check for special characters that need escaping
Test with simple payloads first before complex ones
Conclusion
This lab demonstrated critical vulnerabilities in iOS URL scheme implementations. You learned how attackers exploit weak URL scheme handlers to steal credentials, perform unauthorized actions, and exfiltrate sensitive data. The automated exploitation framework shows how these attacks can be scaled.

Key Takeaways:

Always validate and sanitize URL scheme parameters
Implement signature-based authentication for sensitive operations
Never trust data from URL schemes without verification
Log and monitor URL scheme invocations for suspicious activity
Use allowlists for permitted schemes and actions
Security Best Practices:

Require cryptographic signatures for sensitive URL schemes
Implement rate limiting to prevent automated attacks
Validate all input against strict whitelists
Never log sensitive data like passwords or tokens
Use secure inter-app communication alternatives when possible
